<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 12:32PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Washington and west central Kane Counties through 1245 PM MDT...
At 1232 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of Zion National Park, moving northwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Zion National Park and Springdale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
